                            <comment id="13964962" author="mishail" created="Thu, 10 Apr 2014 04:11:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Nice catch, &lt;tt&gt;cqlsh&lt;/tt&gt; wasn&apos;t updated to support CQL specs after 3.0, the only function it knows is &quot;TOKEN&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
So those blobAsText statements are executed in a different code path, without proper error handling.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As for &lt;tt&gt;token(a) &amp;gt; 0&lt;/tt&gt; query, the tool expect tokens as string literals. Looks like a bug as well.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13972293" author="mishail" created="Thu, 17 Apr 2014 04:12:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching the patch to support the fucntions and BLOB literals&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13974587" author="iamaleksey" created="Fri, 18 Apr 2014 22:43:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
